                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/625.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>First business meeting Central American Conference held 11th. Nicaraguan unable
                    at present attend. Costa Rican secured a rule authorizing deliberative sessions
                    of four members requiring five only for a vote. Discussions planned to last two
                    weeks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
